Business Problem
Many organizations use a third-party time tracking or project management tool (e.g. Primavera, or a bespoke timesheet app) alongside Oracle Fusion PPM. Project costs recorded in the external system need to flow into Fusion PPM so that:

Project managers see accurate cost actuals in real time
Billing and invoicing is based on approved, imported time entries
Project performance dashboards reflect up-to-date KPIs

Oracle Fusion does not natively connect to arbitrary external systems — this integration pattern demonstrates the standard Oracle-recommended approach using the Unprocessed Project Costs REST API + ESS job orchestration, which is the safest and most supportable method for bulk cost ingestion.

## The 7-Step Pattern

| Step | Method | API / Job | Purpose |
|------|--------|-----------|---------|
| 1 | REST POST | `unprocessedProjectCosts` | Upload each transaction to Fusion staging |
| 2 | REST POST | `erpintegrations` (ESS submit) | Trigger the Import Project Costs ESS job |
| 3 | REST GET | `erpintegrations` (ESS status) | Poll until import job completes |
| 4 | REST GET | `erpintegrations` (ESS logs) | Download output/log files for error handling |
| 5 | REST POST | `erpintegrations` (ESS submit) | Trigger Update Project Performance Data job |
| 6 | REST GET | `erpintegrations` (ESS status) | Poll until performance job completes |

## Postman Collection Setup

### 1. Import the Collection
1. Open Postman → **Import** → drag in `INTE-PPM-CostImport.postman_collection.json`

### 2. Create an Environment
Create a Postman Environment and set these variables:

| Variable | Example Value | Notes |
|----------|--------------|-------|
| `fusion_base_url` | `https://[instance].fa.ocs.oraclecloud.com` | Your Fusion Cloud hostname |
| `fusion_username` | `svc_integration_user` | Service account — not a personal login |
| `fusion_password` | *(set as secret)* | Store as Postman Secret, never in plain text |
| `business_unit_name` | `[Your BU Name]` | As configured in Fusion |
| `transaction_source` | `[Your Source Name]` | Configured in PPM Setup |
| `transaction_source_id` | `[ID from Fusion]` | Internal Fusion ID |
| `project_unit_id` | `[ID from Fusion]` | Internal org ID for project unit |
| `expenditure_batch_name` | `MYSOURCE_20250131_001` | Unique per run |
| `project_number` | `[Project Number]` | From `PJF_PROJECTS_ALL_B.segment1` |
| `task_number` | `[Task Number]` | Task within the project |
| `expenditure_type` | `Std Time` | Must exist in Fusion PPM |
| `ess_request_id` | *(populated after Step 3)* | From Step 3 response |
| `ess_performance_request_id` | *(populated after Step 6)* | From Step 6 response |

> ⚠️ **Never store passwords in the collection itself.** Always use Postman Environment Secrets or an external vault (e.g. Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault) in production.

### 3. Run Steps in Order
Execute requests sequentially: Step 1 → 2 → 3 → (poll 4) → 5 (if needed) → 6 → (poll 7)

